## DAW CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT

### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE & FRAMEWORKS

**Technology Stack:**
- **Framework:** React 19.2.4 with TypeScript 5.8.3
- **State Management:** Zustand 5.0.12 (with custom undo system)
- **Build Tool:** Vite 8.0.2
- **Test Runner:** Vitest 4.1.1 with jsdom, React Testing Library
- **Styling:** CSS Modules with CSS Variables (neo-brutalist theme)
- **Validation:** Zod 4.3.6 for runtime type safety

**Directory Structure:**
```
src/
├── audio/                    # Audio engine & synthesis (AudioWorklet-based)
│   ├── synth/               # Synthesizer engine (16 voices, PolyBLEP, ADSR, filters)
│   │   └── dsp/             # DSP algorithms (oscillators, envelopes, filters, LFOs)
│   ├── drum-machine/        # Step sequencer & drum kit
│   ├── mixer/               # Channel strips, metering
│   ├── media-pool/          # Audio file decoding & waveform generation
│   ├── effects/             # Reverb, etc.
│   ├── engine-context.ts    # Main AudioContext wrapper
│   ├── transport-clock.ts   # Sample-accurate timing
│   ├── look-ahead-scheduler.ts # Voice scheduling with lookahead
│   └── message-protocol.ts  # Type-safe MessagePort communication
│
├── state/                    # Application state (Zustand)
│   ├── store.ts             # Main DawStore (tracks, clips, transport)
│   ├── track/               # Track & clip models with Zod schemas
│   ├── undo/                # Undo/redo command system
│   ├── synth/               # Per-track synth parameter state
│   ├── session/             # Session persistence (IndexedDB)
│   └── effects/             # Effects parameter state
│
└── ui/                       # React components
    ├── arrangement/         # Canvas-based arrangement view (E6)
    │   ├── ArrangementPanel.tsx
    │   ├── arrangement-renderer.ts (pure canvas drawing)
    │   ├── use-arrangement-interactions.ts (pointer & drag)
    │   ├── hit-test.ts (spatial queries)
    │   └── constants.ts
    ├── synth/               # Synthesizer UI
    │   ├── SynthEditor.tsx
    │   └── VirtualKeyboard.tsx (2-octave C3-B4)
    ├── transport/           # Transport controls
    ├── mixer/               # Channel strips, master
    ├── drum-machine/        # Step sequencer UI
    ├── primitives/          # Button, Toggle, Modal, Select, etc.
    ├── controls/            # RotaryKnob, Fader, VuMeter
    ├── tokens/              # Design tokens (colors, spacing, fonts)
    └── keyboard/            # Keyboard shortcut system

Import Aliases:
- @/ → src/
- @audio/ → src/audio/
- @ui/ → src/ui/
- @state/ → src/state/
```

---

### 2. EXISTING TRACK SYSTEM & ARRANGEMENT VIEW (E6)

**Track Model** (`src/state/track/types.ts`):
```typescript
type TrackType = "audio" | "instrument";

type TrackModel = {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  type: TrackType;
  color: string;           // hex #rrggbb
  muted: boolean;
  solo: boolean;
  armed: boolean;
  soloIsolate: boolean;
  volume: number;          // 0..2
  pan: number;             // -1..1
  clipIds: readonly string[];
};
```

**Clip Model** (`src/state/track/types.ts`):
```typescript
type ClipModel = {
  id: string;
  trackId: string;
  sourceId: string;        // reference to audio file in media pool
  startTime: number;       // seconds on timeline
  sourceOffset: number;    // seconds into source
  duration: number;        // seconds
  gain: number;            // 0..2
  fadeIn: number;          // seconds
  fadeOut: number;         // seconds
  name: string;
};
```

**Arrangement View Architecture:**
- **Canvas-based renderer** (`arrangement-renderer.ts`):
  - Pure function `renderArrangement(rc: RenderContext)` - no DOM mutations
  - Draws: background, time ruler (bars/beats), grid, track lanes, headers, clips, playhead
  - DPI-aware scaling via `ctx.scale(dpr, dpr)`
  - Supports zoom (10-500 pps), horizontal/vertical scrolling, grid snapping
  - 2px border width, neo-brutalist thick strokes

- **Interaction System** (`use-arrangement-interactions.ts`):
  - Hit-testing for clips, trim handles, track headers, ruler
  - Drag states: `move-clip`, `trim-left`, `trim-right`, `rubber-band`
  - Snap-to-grid with options: "1/4", "1/8", "1/16", "1-bar"
  - Undo integration via `sharedUndoManager.push(cmd)`
  - Cursor feedback: `grab`, `ew-resize`, `default`

- **Hit-Testing** (`hit-test.ts`):
  - `hitTest(x, y, view, tracks, clips)` → HitResult
  - Trim handle detection: 8px from clip edges
  - Reverse iteration (z-order priority)
  - Time conversion: `xToSeconds(x, view)`, `secondsToX(seconds, view)`

- **View State**:
  ```typescript
  type ArrangementViewState = {
    scrollX: number;         // seconds
    scrollY: number;         // pixels
    pixelsPerSecond: number; // zoom level
    trackHeight: number;     // 64px default
    headerWidth: number;     // 160px default
  };
  ```

**Constants** (`constants.ts`):
- `RULER_HEIGHT = 24`
- `CLIP_PADDING = 2`
- `TRIM_HANDLE_PX = 8`

---

### 3. SYNTHESIZER ENGINE (E9)

**Architecture:**
- **16 fixed voices** with voice stealing (oldest-note, 5ms crossfade)
- **Per-voice DSP:**
  - 2× PolyBLEP oscillators (saw, square, sine, triangle)
  - 1× Biquad filter (lowpass, highpass, bandpass)
  - 2× ADSR envelopes (amplitude + filter)
- **Shared:** 2× LFOs (sine, square, triangle, sample-and-hold)
- **Modulation matrix:** LFO1→pitch, LFO2→amplitude, filter envelope→cutoff

**Parameter Map** (`synth-types.ts`):
```typescript
type SynthParameterMap = {
  // Oscillators
  osc1Type: WaveformType;           // "sine" | "saw" | "square" | "triangle"
  osc1Octave: number;               // -2..+2
  osc1Detune: number;               // cents, -100..+100
  osc1Level: number;                // 0..1

  osc2Type: WaveformType;
  osc2Octave: number;
  osc2Detune: number;
  osc2Level: number;

  // Filter
  filterType: FilterType;            // "lowpass" | "highpass" | "bandpass"
  filterCutoff: number;              // Hz, 20..20000
  filterResonance: number;           // Q, 0.5..20

  // Amplitude Envelope (ADSR)
  ampAttack: number;                 // seconds
  ampDecay: number;
  ampSustain: number;                // 0..1
  ampRelease: number;

  // Filter Envelope (ADSR)
  filterAttack: number;
  filterDecay: number;
  filterSustain: number;             // 0..1
  filterRelease: number;
  filterEnvDepth: number;            // semitones, -60..+60

  // LFO 1 (pitch modulation)
  lfo1Rate: number;                  // Hz, 0.1..20
  lfo1Depth: number;                 // 0..1
  lfo1Shape: LFOShape;

  // LFO 2 (amplitude modulation/tremolo)
  lfo2Rate: number;
  lfo2Depth: number;
  lfo2Shape: LFOShape;

  // Global
  glideTime: number;                 // pitch glide, 0..1 seconds
  masterGain: number;                // 0..1
};
```

**Voice Commands** (main thread → worklet):
```typescript
type SynthVoiceCommand =
  | { type: "noteOn"; note: number; velocity: number; legato: boolean }
  | { type: "noteOff"; note: number }
  | { type: "allNotesOff" }
  | { type: "setParam"; key: string; value: number };
```

**Main Thread Interface** (`synth-instrument.ts`):
```typescript
type SynthInstrument = {
  output: AudioNode;  // connect to mixer
  params: Readonly<SynthParameterMap>;
  noteOn(note: number, velocity: number, legato?: boolean): void;
  noteOff(note: number): void;
  allNotesOff(): void;
  setParam<K extends keyof SynthParameterMap>(key: K, value: SynthParameterMap[K]): void;
  connectToMixer(mixer: MixerEngine, trackId: string): void;
  dispose(): void;
};
```

**AudioWorklet Processor** (`synth-processor.ts`):
- Registered as `"synth-processor"`
- Zero-allocation in `process()` method
- Voice allocator with crossfade on steal
- Filter coefficients computed at block rate (not per-sample)
- Pitch glide (exponential smoothing)

**MIDI Conversion:**
```typescript
export function midiToFreq(note: number): number {
  return 440 * Math.pow(2, (note - 69) / 12);  // A4=69=440Hz
}
```

---

### 4. DESIGN SYSTEM (E2) - NEO-BRUTALIST THEME

**Color Palette** (`tokens.ts` & `tokens.css`):
```javascript
{
