1173	The arrangement view renders the timeline as a 2D canvas where:
1174	
1175	- **X axis** = time (beats or seconds)
1176	- **Y axis** = tracks
1177	
1178	The viewport is defined by `{ scrollBeats, scrollTrackIndex, pixelsPerBeat, trackHeightPx }`. All rendering is relative to the viewport.
1179	
1180	```typescript
1181	interface ViewportState {
1182	  scrollBeats: number;       // leftmost visible beat position
1183	  scrollTrackIndex: number;  // topmost visible track index
1184	  pixelsPerBeat: number;     // zoom level
1185	  trackHeightPx: number;
1186	  canvasWidth: number;
1187	  canvasHeight: number;
1188	}
1189	
1190	function beatsToPixels(beats: number, viewport: ViewportState): number {
1191	  return (beats - viewport.scrollBeats) * viewport.pixelsPerBeat;
1192	}
1193	
1194	function pixelsToBeats(pixels: number, viewport: ViewportState): number {
1195	  return pixels / viewport.pixelsPerBeat + viewport.scrollBeats;
1196	}
1197	```
1198	
1199	### 8.2 Zoom and Scroll
1200	
1201	Zoom should be centered on the mouse cursor position (pinch-to-zoom on trackpad), maintaining the beat position under the cursor:
1202	
1203	```typescript
1204	function zoomAroundPoint(
1205	  viewport: ViewportState,
1206	  pivotPixels: number,
1207	  zoomFactor: number
1208	): ViewportState {
1209	  const pivotBeats = pixelsToBeats(pivotPixels, viewport);
1210	  const newPixelsPerBeat = viewport.pixelsPerBeat * zoomFactor;
1211	  // After zoom, pivotBeats must still map to pivotPixels
1212	  const newScrollBeats = pivotBeats - pivotPixels / newPixelsPerBeat;
1213	  return { ...viewport, pixelsPerBeat: newPixelsPerBeat, scrollBeats: newScrollBeats };
1214	}
1215	```
1216	
1217	For large sessions (10,000+ clips), rendering all clips every frame is too slow. A spatial index (interval tree or R-tree on the beat axis) enables efficient viewport culling:
1218	
1219	```typescript
1220	function getVisibleClips(clips: AudioClip[], viewport: ViewportState): AudioClip[] {
1221	  const startBeats = viewport.scrollBeats;
1222	  const endBeats = startBeats + viewport.canvasWidth / viewport.pixelsPerBeat;
1223	  // Interval tree query: clips overlapping [startBeats, endBeats]
1224	  return clipIntervalTree.query(startBeats, endBeats);
1225	}
1226	```
1227	
1228	At extreme zoom-out, clips smaller than 1 pixel are merged into a "density visualization" similar to Ableton Live's arrangement view at low zoom.
1229	
1230	### 8.3 Snap-to-Grid
1231	
1232	Snap maps a raw beat position to the nearest grid line:
1233	
1234	```typescript
1235	type GridResolution =
1236	  | { type: 'bar' }
1237	  | { type: 'beat' }
1238	  | { type: 'subdivision'; subdivisions: number }  // e.g. 4 = 1/4 beat
1239	  | { type: 'triplet'; base: number }               // triplet grid
1240	  | { type: 'none' };
1241	
1242	function snapToGrid(
1243	  positionBeats: number,
1244	  resolution: GridResolution,
1245	  beatsPerBar: number
1246	): number {
1247	  const gridSize = getGridSizeBeats(resolution, beatsPerBar);
1248	  if (gridSize <= 0) return positionBeats;
1249	  return Math.round(positionBeats / gridSize) * gridSize;
1250	}
1251	
1252	function getGridSizeBeats(resolution: GridResolution, beatsPerBar: number): number {
1253	  switch (resolution.type) {
1254	    case 'bar': return beatsPerBar;
1255	    case 'beat': return 1;
1256	    case 'subdivision': return 1 / resolution.subdivisions;
1257	    case 'triplet': return (2 / 3) / resolution.base;
1258	    case 'none': return 0;
1259	  }
1260	}
1261	```
1262	
1263	**Magnetic snap** (Ableton Live) applies a "gravity well" effect: the snap is only engaged if the cursor is within a threshold distance of the nearest grid line.
1264	
1265	```typescript
1266	function magneticSnap(
1267	  positionBeats: number,
1268	  resolution: GridResolution,
1269	  viewport: ViewportState,
1270	  magnetThresholdPx: number = 8
1271	): number {
1272	  const gridSize = getGridSizeBeats(resolution, /* ... */);
1273	  const snapped = snapToGrid(positionBeats, resolution, /* ... */);
1274	  const distancePx = Math.abs(snapped - positionBeats) * viewport.pixelsPerBeat;
1275	  return distancePx <= magnetThresholdPx ? snapped : positionBeats;
1276	}
1277	```
