1294	### 8.5 Automation Lanes
1295	
1296	Automation lanes are sub-rows beneath a track displaying parameter automation as breakpoint curves.
1297	
1298	```typescript
1299	interface AutomationLane {
1300	  id: string;
1301	  trackId: string;
1302	  parameterId: string;    // e.g., "fader", "pan", "plugin-1.param-3"
1303	  parameterName: string;
1304	  visible: boolean;
1305	  height: number;         // in pixels
1306	  breakpoints: AutomationPoint[];
1307	  interpolation: 'linear' | 'exponential' | 'step' | 'bezier';
1308	}
1309	
1310	interface AutomationPoint {
1311	  positionBeats: number;
1312	  value: number;          // normalized [0, 1] within parameter range
1313	  curveType?: 'ease-in' | 'ease-out' | 'ease-in-out'; // for bezier segments
1314	}
1315	```
1316	
1317	Automation evaluation at a given beat position:
1318	
1319	```typescript
1320	function evaluateAutomation(lane: AutomationLane, positionBeats: number): number {
1321	  if (lane.breakpoints.length === 0) return 0.5;
1322	  if (positionBeats <= lane.breakpoints[0].positionBeats) return lane.breakpoints[0].value;
1323	  const last = lane.breakpoints[lane.breakpoints.length - 1];
1324	  if (positionBeats >= last.positionBeats) return last.value;
1325	
1326	  // Binary search for enclosing segment
1327	  let lo = 0, hi = lane.breakpoints.length - 2;
1328	  while (lo < hi) {
1329	    const mid = (lo + hi + 1) >> 1;
1330	    if (lane.breakpoints[mid].positionBeats <= positionBeats) lo = mid;
1331	    else hi = mid - 1;
1332	  }
1333	
1334	  const p0 = lane.breakpoints[lo];
1335	  const p1 = lane.breakpoints[lo + 1];
1336	  const t = (positionBeats - p0.positionBeats) / (p1.positionBeats - p0.positionBeats);
1337	  return interpolate(p0.value, p1.value, t, lane.interpolation);
1338	}
1339	```
1340	
1341	**Ableton Live** uses breakpoint-based automation with linear, exponential, and bezier curve handles. **Logic Pro** uses "Hyper Draw" for simple automation and a full "Automation Editor" for complex curves. **Reaper** supports custom envelope shapes per segment.
