tool_use_result.prompt:
You need to fix critical P0/P1 review findings in a DAW project's piano roll implementation. Fix ALL of these issues:

## Fix 1: Undo command monkey-patching (P0 - data corruption)

File: `src/ui/piano-roll/use-piano-roll-interactions.ts`

The onPointerUp handler monkey-patches `cmd.execute` on MoveNoteCommand and ResizeNoteCommand, which means `oldStartTime`, `oldPitch`, and `oldDuration` are never captured during execute(). Undo will then revert to 0/0/0 instead of the original values.

**Solution**: Refactor MoveNoteCommand and ResizeNoteCommand in `src/state/track/midi-commands.ts` to accept pre-captured old values, so they don't need execute() to be called to capture state. Then in the interaction hook, construct the command with the pre-captured values and push it without calling execute() (since the store is already updated during drag).

In `src/state/track/midi-commands.ts`, change MoveNoteCommand:
```typescript
export class MoveNoteCommand implements UndoCommand {
  readonly type = "move-note";
  private oldStartTime: number;
  private oldPitch: number;

  constructor(
    private readonly clipId: string,
    private readonly noteId: string,
    private readonly newStartTime: number,
    private readonly newPitch: number,
    oldStartTime?: number,
    oldPitch?: number,
  ) {
    this.oldStartTime = oldStartTime ?? 0;
    this.oldPitch = oldPitch ?? 0;
  }

  execute(): void {
    const clip = getStore().clips[this.clipId];
    if (clip && isMidiClip(clip)) {
      const note = clip.noteEvents.find((n) => n.id === this.noteId);
      if (note && this.oldStartTime === 0 && this.oldPitch === 0) {
        // Only capture if not pre-set via constructor
        this.oldStartTime = note.startTime;
        this.oldPitch = note.pitch;
      }
    }
    getStore().moveNoteEvent(this.clipId, this.noteId, this.newStartTime, this.newPitch);
  }
  // ... undo and serialize stay the same
}
```

Wait, actually the simplest fix: add optional `oldStartTime` and `oldPitch` constructor params that pre-populate the private fields. If provided, execute() skips re-capturing. Same for ResizeNoteCommand with `oldDuration`.

Then in `use-piano-roll-interactions.ts`, when creating the command on pointer up during move-note drag:
```typescript
const cmd = new MoveNoteCommand(
  drag.clipId, drag.noteId, 
  note.startTime, note.pitch,
  drag.origStartTime, drag.origPitch  // pre-captured old values
);
// Don't call cmd.execute() - store is already updated
sharedUndoManager.push(cmd);
```

Remove the monkey-patching of `cmd.execute`.

Same pattern for ResizeNoteCommand.

## Fix 2: Store note mutations accept unclamped values (P1)

File: `src/state/store.ts`

Add clamping to all note mutation methods:

```typescript
// In moveNoteEvent:
const clampedPitch = Math.max(0, Math.min(127, Math.round(newPitch)));
const clampedStartTime = Math.max(0, newStartTime);

// In resizeNoteEvent:
const clampedDuration = Math.max(0.01, newDuration);

// In updateNoteVelocity:
const clampedVelocity = Math.max(0, Math.min(127, Math.round(velocity)));

// In addNoteEvent - clamp all fields:
const clampedNote: MIDINoteEvent = {
  ...note,
  pitch: Math.max(0, Math.min(127, Math.round(note.pitch))),
  velocity: Math.max(0, Math.min(127, Math.round(note.velocity))),
  startTime: Math.max(0, note.startTime),
  duration: Math.max(0.01, note.duration),
};
```

## Fix 3: stopRecording() zero/negative duration notes (P1)

File: `src/audio/midi/midi-recorder.ts`

In `stopRecording()`, when closing open notes, clamp duration to minimum 0.01 and filter out any degenerate notes:

```typescript
// When closing open notes in stopRecording:
const duration = Math.max(0.01, lastMessageTime - open.startAbsolute);
```

Also add the same guard in the note-off handling during recording.

## Fix 4: Recorder keys by pitch only, ignoring channel (P1)

File: `src/audio/midi/midi-recorder.ts`

Change the `openNotes` map key from just `note` to `channel * 128 + note`:
```typescript
// note-on:
const key = message.channel * 128 + message.note;
openNotes.set(key, { ... });

// note-off:
const key = message.channel * 128 + message.note;
const open = openNotes.get(key);
```

## Implementation Steps

1. Read each file before editing
2. Make all the fixes
3. Run `pnpm test -- --run` to verify all tests still pass
4. Run `pnpm lint` to check lint
5. Run `pnpm prettier --write "src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"` if needed

Make sure NOT to break existing test expectations. If tests need updating to match the new behavior (e.g., the clamping), update them too.
